Header: SGDID:S000000195 DisplayId=YBL099W Aliases=ATP1 Annotaion=None Description=Alpha subunit of the F1 sector of mitochondrial F1F0 ATP synthase; which is a large, evolutionarily conserved enzyme complex required for ATP synthesis; F1 translationally regulates ATP6 and ATP8 expression to achieve a balanced output of ATP synthase genes encoded in nucleus and mitochondria; phosphorylated; N-terminally propionylated in vivo

SGDID:S000003882 DisplayId=YJR121W Aliases=ATP2 Annotaion=None Description=Beta subunit of the F1 sector of mitochondrial F1F0 ATP synthase; which is a large, evolutionarily conserved enzyme complex required for ATP synthesis; F1 translationally regulates ATP6 and ATP8 expression to achieve a balanced output of ATP synthase genes encoded in nucleus and mitochondria; phosphorylated

SGDID:S000005591 DisplayId=YOR065W Aliases=CYT1 Annotaion=None Description=Cytochrome c1; component of the mitochondrial respiratory chain; expression is regulated by the heme-activated, glucose-repressed Hap2p/3p/4p/5p CCAAT-binding complex

SGDID:S000000956 DisplayId=YER154W Aliases=OXA1 Annotaion=None Description=Mitochondrial inner membrane insertase; mediates the insertion of both mitochondrial- and nuclear-encoded proteins from the matrix into the inner membrane; also has a role in insertion of carrier proteins into the inner membrane; acts as a voltage-gated ion channel, activated by substrate peptides; interacts with mitochondrial ribosomes; conserved from bacteria to animals

SGDID:S000000118 DisplayId=YBL022C Aliases=PIM1 Annotaion=None Description=ATP-dependent Lon protease; involved in degradation of misfolded proteins in mitochondria; required for biogenesis and maintenance of mitochondria

SGDID:S000000126 DisplayId=YBL030C Aliases=PET9 Annotaion=None Description=Major ADP/ATP carrier of the mitochondrial inner membrane; exchanges cytosolic ADP for mitochondrially synthesized ATP; also imports heme and ATP; phosphorylated; required for viability in many lab strains that carry a sal1 mutation; PET9 has a paralog, AAC3, that arose from the whole genome duplication

SGDID:S000002357 DisplayId=YDL198C Aliases=GGC1 Annotaion=None Description=Mitochondrial GTP/GDP transporter; essential for mitochondrial genome maintenance; has a role in mitochondrial iron transport; member of the mitochondrial carrier family

SGDID:S000001603 DisplayId=YKL120W Aliases=OAC1 Annotaion=None Description=Mitochondrial inner membrane transporter; transports oxaloacetate, sulfate, thiosulfate, and isopropylmalate; member of the mitochondrial carrier family

SGDID:S000003838 DisplayId=YJR077C Aliases=MIR1 Annotaion=None Description=Mitochondrial phosphate carrier; imports inorganic phosphate into mitochondria; functionally redundant with Pic2p but more abundant than Pic2p under normal conditions; phosphorylated

SGDID:S000000855 DisplayId=YER053C Aliases=PIC2 Annotaion=None Description=Mitochondrial copper and phosphate carrier; imports copper and inorganic phosphate into mitochondria; functionally redundant with Mir1p but less abundant than Mir1p under normal conditions; expression is induced at high temperature

SGDID:S000004295 DisplayId=YLR304C Aliases=ACO1 Annotaion=None Description=Aconitase; required for the tricarboxylic acid (TCA) cycle and also independently required for mitochondrial genome maintenance; phosphorylated; component of the mitochondrial nucleoid; mutation leads to glutamate auxotrophy

SGDID:S000000943 DisplayId=YER141W Aliases=COX15 Annotaion=None Description=Protein required for the hydroxylation of heme O to form heme A; heme A is an essential prosthetic group for cytochrome c oxidase

SGDID:S000000241 DisplayId=YBR037C Aliases=SCO1 Annotaion=None Description=Copper-binding protein of mitochondrial inner membrane; required for cytochrome c oxidase activity and respiration; may function to deliver copper to cytochrome c oxidase; similar to thioredoxins; SCO1 has a paralog, SCO2, that arose from the whole genome duplication

SGDID:S000003159 DisplayId=YGL191W Aliases=COX13 Annotaion=None Description=Subunit VIa of cytochrome c oxidase; present in a subclass of cytochrome c oxidase complexes that may have a role in mimimizing generation of reactive oxygen species; not essential for cytochrome c oxidase activity but may modulate activity in response to ATP; required for assembly of Rcf2p into cytochrome c oxidase - cytochrome bc1 supercomplexes
